Frontend Scope:
React, Progressive Web App (PWA), Service Worker, offline-first user
interface, local browser storage, local cache, synchronization queue,
queued requests, sync conflict UX, and related frontend assets.

Humanitarian Context:
This frontend is part of Projetos Humanitários Open Source.

It was created to support emergency response scenarios where hospitals,
shelters, donors, medical teams, volunteers, and affected communities may
have unstable or unavailable internet access.

The initial humanitarian motivation includes support for people affected by
the earthquake crisis in Venezuela, where hospitals may be damaged and
medical supplies may be distributed across shelters, donors, support centers,
and emergency teams.

Offline-First Purpose:
The purpose is to allow shelters, donors, hospitals, and medical teams to
continue recording medical supply offers and urgent demands while offline,
and to synchronize the data with the MedSupply Relay backend when internet
access returns.

MVP User Flow:
- Supply screen: shelters and donors register available medicines and supplies.
- Demand screen: hospitals and medical teams register urgent needs.
- Offline mode: users continue entering essential information without internet.
- Sync mode: pending records are synchronized when connectivity is restored.
- Matching result: the system shows matches between supply and demand.
- Reservation flow: teams reserve stock before pickup to avoid double allocation.
- Export flow: coordination can export TXT/CSV contingency files.

Acceptance Criterion:
If Hospital Y needs Paracetamol
And Shelter X has Paracetamol
Then the system returns a simple match:
"Shelter X has the Paracetamol that Hospital Y needs."

